Today is my moms birthday!! I remember being very young and when my brothers and sisters went to school it was just me and her. She would let me choose a record and I usually would go with the Beatles. They were hers from when she was young. I would dance around and sing and she would laugh. She always believed in my musical abilities and would encourage me, except when I was in high school but we don’t need to get into that! Nevertheless she is a thoughtful and wonderful woman and I couldn’t be more proud to be her son. Happy birthday mom! I love you very much!

When I was a kid I used to look back on days before me and study them. In particular hockey was a large interest of mine and my hero of that era was none other than Bobby Hull. I wanted to play with his tenacity and thought he was the quintessential hockey player. When I was 11 or so he came to a trading card show in Kalamazoo Michigan to sign autographs, and sure enough I was there with my father, 3rd in line to note, to shake his hand and get a signature from him. I had purchased a Tony Esposito card before I got in line and it was in my other hand when we met. He said “Hey, who’s that old timer you got there?” I was thrilled he said anything to me about the card in my hand and told me Tony was a great teammate. I then handed him the glossy 8x10 I had of him and watched him sign “To my buddy Dave” on it. I was over the moon! I still have the photograph he signed for me as well as the Esposito card. Later on I learned my grandfather used to do some events with the hawks with the lions club and my aunt sent me a photo of grandpa with Hull brothers. I have it framed on my living room wall to this day. RIP to my favorite hockey player of all time.

Friends, I just want to say thank you for all the well wishes the past month. I never was specific about my surgery that happened March 9, so just to let you know I had some nerve damage in my left elbow and carpal tunnel in my hand that was causing me a lot of pain while I performed over the years. It was time to correct it. I had a splint and sling on for almost 3 weeks it’s been off for 2 weeks now. I’ve have been healing up nicely and I am now able to play guitar again for about 15 minutes a day!! Feels good to get back at it after so many weeks with having that ability. Thanks again to everyone has been checking in, it means a lot to me. I’ll see you all soon!

Yesterday I was at a family get together. It was so nice to see my cousins, aunts, and uncles. I’m truly grateful for them and I feel lucky today. Just sitting around and talking going through old photos and bringing up memories of family who have passed on or the ones who couldn’t make it. I said I was lucky, and that put in perspective how much family I have that aren’t related by blood, and I’m truly grateful for all of my extended family as well. It’s the time of year where everyone deserves family and not everyone has that. Please check in with your loved ones. Let them know you’re there, I’m here and I love you all.

Looking forward to getting back to Michigan to close out the year!! Saginaw with @may_erlewine and Detroit  with @fullcordband and two very special nights in my hometown of just 6reensky!!! See all then!!

Being the end of the year I have been spending time with my family. All of my family! My music community, my mother and father, brothers and sisters, nieces nephews, and cousins aunts and uncles. I feel grateful to have so much in my life. Everyday I’m grateful for all of the support and the people in my life showing up for me. I wouldn’t be here today without that. I know that not everyone has that, and if you don’t I am here for you. To listen, talk, or whatever you need from me. And I’m thankful for today being my 1212 day continuous without alcohol. Thank you all for the help along the way, the ears to hear me and the wisdom and kind words I have heard the past 3 years. I never thought I’d be here, and I’m so happy I asked for help when I did. I love you all, and I’m here for you if you need it. I want everyone to feel safe, loved, and seen. I’m here for you.

How did I get so lucky? I met @phoffmanmusic at an open mic in Kalamazoo MI in 2000 23 years later here we are. Countless miles, songs, laughs, arguments later he’s still my little brother. I wouldn’t be who I am without you Paul. I’m proud of you for the work you’ve done and always inspiring me to go a little farther and to live. Thank you for supporting me and having my back everyday. I love you so much and I hope you have a wonderful day today. Happy birthday little bro.

Kalamazoo MI my hometown. I am grateful to be returning to the @kazoostate theatre for our new years shows this year. I’m full of love and excitement today. The list of legends I have witnessed at this venue when I was growing up, helped shaped me as a person and as a musician. And to have our dear friend and collaborator @hollyjbowling with us is just icing on the cake. As we wrap up 2023, remember to breathe, to love, shine, be open to it all and let it go all at once. Recently I have been reminded and inspired by a friend to remember what being a musician actually means, not that I have forgot, but to see that again has made a profound impact on me and I want to shine for you as you do for me. I love you all! I can’t wait to share our music with you in a building that shaped me and showed me what is possible to making art. Happy new year everyone!
